# Map personal email addresses to the GitHub noreply form so they are not
# globally indexed once this repo is public. The Noreply form `<userid>+<login>
# @users.noreply.github.com` is the canonical GitHub-friendly identity and still
# correctly attributes commits to the account in the GitHub UI.
#
# This is a display-layer fix: raw commit objects still carry the original
# email. A full history rewrite (git filter-repo) would be needed to redact
# the raw objects, but that invalidates all branches/PRs/stashes. The mailmap
# defends against the realistic spam-scraping threat (GitHub web UI + API),
# which is what we care about here.

Ruben Lütke <226271791+rubenluetke10-beep@users.noreply.github.com> <ruben.luetke10@gmail.com>
